1-.
Type Casting= The process of converting one datatype to another datatype is called Type casting.

There are two types 1. Implicit Type Casting and 
                                  2.Explicit Type Casting.

Implicit Type Casting-The process of conversion of lower datatype to higher datatype.

Ex-
byte a=20;
int i= a;
System.out.println(a+" "+i);
Output-20 20.

Explicit Type Casting-The process of conversion of higher datatype to lower datatype.

Ex-
int i= 25;
byte a=(byte)i;
System.out.println(a+" "+i);
Output-25 25.

3-> In java , class  variable has a default value , while in the case of local variable we need to first initialize it otherwise it will give an error.
For ex-
a-> 
int i=20;
int j;
if(i==20) {
	j=12;
}
 System.out.println(j)
output-The local variable j has not been initialized.
b->
int i=20;
		int j;
		if(i==20) {
			j=12;
		}else {
			j=99;
		}
	    System.out.println(j);
output-No Compilation error.
